parameters.name: partner_id
parameters.description: Partner ID is assigned upon registration is successful

parameters.name: access_token
parameters.description: This token ID for access using to identify your permission to do so. Visit our Console and you will find it in your console.

parameters.name: sign
parameters.description: Signature generated by partner_id, api sign, timestamp, access_token using a md5 method. Sign = md5(partner_id + API_SIGN_SECRET + access_token + timestamp)

response_fields.name: error
response_fields.description: Indicate error info if any error happened

response_fields.name: message
response_fields.description: Indicate error detail info if any error happened

response_fields.name: type
response_fields.description: This identifier for get request id.

response_fields.name: total_count
response_fields.description: Total number of orders that match the condition

response_fields.name: next_cursor
response_fields.description: Pass the next_cursor in the next request to continue get the next page data

response_fields.name: msg_id
response_fields.description: List of number that match the condition

response_fields.name: sha_name
response_fields.description: Shopper's unique identifier for all item

response_fields.name: model_id
response_fields.description: Shopper's unique identifier for a model under item

response_fields.name: unscraped_sha_id
response_fields.description: Unscraped SHA ID of the model

notes: The documentation shows both request parameters and response fields in detail. The API appears to be for retrieving unpaid orders with pagination support through next_cursor parameter.
